    editCellValue(char) - Method in class Table
    edit the selected cell's value
    editColAttributes(char) - Method in class Table
    Edits the value of the selected field with the given character If selected field is: Name: appends character or delete last character if backspace Type: cycles through allowed values regardless of input Allow blanks: Inverts the allowed value regardless of input Default value: If the type is name/field: appends character or deletes last character if backspace was pressed If the type is integer: same behaviour but only accepts numerical characters and backspace If the type is boolean: cycles through allowed values
    editDefaultValue(char) - Method in class Column
    Edits the default value: If type is string/email: append character or remove last character if given character is backspace.
    editName(char) - Method in class Column
    appends given character to name, deletes last character if the given character is backspace.
    editName(char) - Method in class Table

    editTableName(char) - Method in class TableManager
    edit selected table's name
    editValue(char, String) - Method in class Cell
    Edits the cell's value: If given type is string/email/boolean: append character or remove last character if given character is backspace.
